snippet.textDisplay:
Saw 1-3 were amazing, 4 was alright. 5 was okay. 6 was great in my opinion but gets a bad rep because of 4 & 5 going downhill a bit. 7 was just okay, but unfortunately didnt feel like a good ending for the original saga.
Jigsaw was actually pretty dope, although i feel like it needs a sequel so that a new saga can form out of it. Now there's Spiral, which I wonder if its a sequel to Jigsaw or not. Because Logan is still out there in Jigsaw, as is Dr. Gordon. Hoffman is likely dead. Anyways, i really hope they dont just abandon the Logan Nelson storyline. Because he felt a bit like Dexter meets Jigsaw. Like a killer with specific motives that wants to take on the Jigsaw role, but has his own code too. I would love it if Logan was the killer in Spiral. We already know from Jigsaw that he hates corrupt cops. Therefore it wouldn't be a stretch to make him the killer. So i really really hope its him and not some new guy/girl. Idk, it would be nice if they could do that. Like Saw 1-7 is the legacy of the original Jigsaw. Then Jigsaw is the passing of the crown to his successor... And then finally Spiral, the first chapter in a new saga with Logan Nelson as the new Jigsaw, somewhat honoring his mentor's legacy by going after corruption and injustice in the world.

Probably wont be the case, but if it was that would be awesome. Either way, i'll be watching this for sure :)
